<div data-fuse="Article_Incontent_4"></div></div>
<h3><a href="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/existentialcrises.png"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="262684" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-was-literary-twitter-the-bracketwhat-was-literary-twitter-the-bracket/existentialcrises/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/existentialcrises.png" data-orig-size="1200,76" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="existentialcrises" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/existentialcrises-300x19.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/existentialcrises.png" class="aligncenter wp-image-262684" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/existentialcrises-300x19.png" alt="" width="800" height="51" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/existentialcrises-300x19.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/existentialcrises-768x49.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/existentialcrises-60x4.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/existentialcrises-50x3.png 50w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/existentialcrises.png 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></a></h3>
<hr />
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong>#PublishingPaidMe (9) </strong><strong>vs. is it ableist to say writers should read? (10)</strong></h2>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263160" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-was-literary-twitter-the-bracket-day-4/publishingpaidwritersread/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/publishingpaidwritersread.png" data-orig-size="1200,403" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="publishingpaidwritersread" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/publishingpaidwritersread-300x101.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/publishingpaidwritersread.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-263160" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/publishingpaidwritersread.png" alt="" width="1200" height="403" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/publishingpaidwritersread.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/publishingpaidwritersread-300x101.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/publishingpaidwritersread-768x258.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/publishingpaidwritersread-60x20.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/publishingpaidwritersread-50x17.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></p>
<h2>#PublishingPaidMe (9)</h2>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;"><b>Trending Because:</b> At its best, Twitter was amazing as an organizing tool: you could yell at powerful people who were usually holed away in their ivory towers and you could share information they were trying to hide from the rest of us. Black writer <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/L.L._McKinney" class="external" target="_blank">L.L. McKinney</a> started the hashtag <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PublishingPaidMe" class="external" target="_blank">#PublishingPaidMe</a> to draw attention to the disparity between what Black and white authors were getting paid for deals. And it took off: Big name authors joined in to share what they made, and it got the attention of publications like <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2020/06/08/books/publishingpaidme-publishing-day-of-action.html" class="external" target="_blank"><em>The Times</em></a><em>, <a href="https://www.npr.org/2020/06/08/872470156/-publishingpaidme-authors-share-their-advances-to-expose-racial-disparities" class="external" target="_blank">NPR</a>, </em>and<em> <a href="https://www.vulture.com/2020/06/publishingpaidme-takes-twitter-with-roxane-gay-other-authors.html" class="external" target="_blank">Vulture</a></em> too. As much as people poo-pooed Twitter organizing as slacktivism, this sort of crowd-sourced transparency had its uses.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;"><b>Retweeted by:</b> The angry and underpaid</p>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong>VS.</strong></h2>
<h2>is it ableist to say writers should read? (10)</h2>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;"><b>Trending Because:</b> The trick to Twitter was to be <i>just</i> popular enough. There has always been a hard ceiling on the benefits of virality: you want to be popular, but <a href="https://x.com/maplecocaine/status/1080665226410889217?s=20" class="external" target="_blank">never the main character.</a></p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">One of the most searing examples of this dynamic was when Ana Mardoll got the main character treatment after posting <a href="https://i.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/original/002/413/875/e51.jpg" class="external" target="_blank">a now deleted Tweet</a> saying it’s ableist to expect writers to read. Weird stuff, by all accounts, and this was such an <a href="https://x.com/AlexanderMcCoy4/status/1553918627581149185" class="external" target="_blank">attention</a>-grabbing <a href="https://x.com/peligrietzer/status/1553864500926988288" class="external" target="_blank">take</a> that it also led people to discover that Mardoll was a neoptism hire at the giant weapons company Lockeed Martin, in addition to being a writer. If you don&#8217;t remember the details (and want to), <a href="https://www.mic.com/culture/why-is-lockheed-martin-the-twitter-person-of-the-day" class="external" target="_blank">Brandon Yu helpfully rounded up the whole story here</a>.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">Writing, building bombs, <i>and</i> posting wild takes? That’s the American Dream right there.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px; text-align: left;"><b>Retweeted by:</b> Drone pilots who love YA</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><iframe loading="lazy" src="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeoIXm89Jwz289JdywENlf2d3-TXPBhmvFq0C_YCIzJfYUJ5g/viewform?embedded=true" frameborder="0" width="640" height="461" marginheight="0" marginwidth="0" allowfullscreen="true" mozallowfullscreen="true" webkitallowfullscreen="true"></iframe></p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;">*</h1>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="262697" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-was-literary-twitter-the-bracketwhat-was-literary-twitter-the-bracket/mattersoftaste/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/mattersoftaste.png" data-orig-size="1200,76" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="mattersoftaste" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/mattersoftaste-300x19.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/mattersoftaste.png" class="aligncenter wp-image-262697" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/mattersoftaste-300x19.png" alt="" width="800" height="51" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/mattersoftaste-300x19.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/mattersoftaste-768x49.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/mattersoftaste-60x4.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/mattersoftaste-50x3.png 50w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/mattersoftaste.png 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></h2>
